prep_instructions.1: Whisk vinegar, chili powder, oil, 2 teaspoons salt and garlic powder in a 9-by-13-inch baking dish. Add steak and turn to coat. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour and up to 24 hours.
prep_instructions.2: Make salsa about 20 minutes (and up to 2 hours) before cooking the meat: Gently combine tomatoes, jalapenos (or chiles) to taste, onion, cilantro, avocado, lime juice and the remaining ¾ teaspoon salt in a medium bowl.
prep_instructions.3: Position rack in upper third of oven; preheat broiler.
prep_instructions.4: Place the steak on a rimmed baking sheet (discard the marinade). Broil 3 to 4 minutes per side for medium. Transfer to a clean cutting board and let rest for 5 minutes. Thinly slice against the grain. Serve the steak wrapped in warm tortillas and topped with the salsa and cheese.

prep_instructions.1: Combine pasta, broth, milk, salt and pepper in an electric pressure cooker. Close and lock the lid. Cook at high pressure for 7 minutes.
prep_instructions.2: Release the pressure. Add broccoli, Cheddar and cream cheese. Stir until the cheese has melted. Let stand for 5 minutes. Stir again and serve.

prep_instructions.1: Cut chicken in half crosswise and sprinkle with ¼ teaspoon each salt and pepper. Place flour on a plate and dredge both sides of the chicken in it. Shake off any excess. Whisk tomato paste and ⅓ cup water in a small bowl and place near the stove.
prep_instructions.2: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the chicken and cook, turning once, until browned on both sides, about 10 minutes. Transfer to a plate.
prep_instructions.3: Add sopressata (or salami) to the pan and cook, stirring, until browned, 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in the tomato paste mixture and lemon. Return the chicken to the pan, cover and cook, turning once, until the sauce has thickened and an instant-read thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the chicken registers 165°F, 5 to 7 minutes.

4.name of recipe: Lentil & Roasted Vegetable Salad with Green Goddess Dressing

prep_instructions.1: Preheat oven to 400°F.
prep_instructions.2: Toss broccoli and green beans with oil and ¼ teaspoon each salt and pepper on a large rimmed baking sheet. Roast, stirring once, until tender, about 20 minutes.
prep_instructions.3: Meanwhile, bring water and lentils to a boil in a medium saucepan over high heat. Reduce heat to a simmer, cover and cook until tender, about 25 minutes. Rinse and drain well.
prep_instructions.4: Combine herbs, mayonnaise, buttermilk, lemon juice, miso, garlic and the remaining ¼ teaspoon each salt and pepper in a food processor or blender. Process until smooth.
prep_instructions.5: Gently toss escarole (or lettuce) and kale with the roasted vegetables and lentils in a large bowl. Serve with the dressing.

5.name of recipe: Smoky Shrimp, Corn & Pea One-Pot Pasta

prep_instructions.1: Combine pasta, shrimp, spinach, corn, peas, onion, garlic, tomato paste, paprika, saffron and salt in a large pot. Stir in water. Bring to a boil over high heat. Boil, stirring frequently, until the pasta is cooked and the water has almost evaporated, 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Serve sprinkled with parsley.

6.name of recipe: Roasted Chicken Thighs, Potatoes & Scallions with Herb Vinaigrette

prep_instructions.1: Preheat oven to 450°F.
prep_instructions.2: Toss potatoes and scallions with 4 teaspoons oil and ¼ teaspoon each pepper and salt in a large bowl. Spread evenly on a large rimmed baking sheet. Place chicken on top; drizzle with 2 teaspoons oil and sprinkle with ¼ teaspoon each pepper and salt. Roast until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the thickest part registers 165°F and the potatoes are tender, 18 to 20 minutes.
prep_instructions.3: Meanwhile, whisk the remaining 2 tablespoons oil and ¼ teaspoon pepper with vinegar, herbs, mustard and shallot in a small bowl. Serve drizzled over the chicken and vegetables.

7.name of recipe: Beef Kofta with Bulgar & Kale Salad

prep_instructions.1: Bring water and bulgur to a boil in a medium saucepan. Cover, reduce heat to maintain a simmer and cook until tender, about 12 minutes. Drain any excess liquid. Spread on a rimmed baking sheet to cool for 10 minutes.
prep_instructions.2: Position rack in upper third of oven. Preheat broiler to high.
prep_instructions.3: Transfer 1 cup of the bulgur to a medium bowl. Add beef, chopped onion, garlic, cumin, ½ teaspoon salt and ¼ teaspoon pepper to the bowl; gently knead together until just combined. (Do not overmix.) With damp hands, form the mixture into 8 cigar-shaped patties, 4 inches long and 1½ inches thick. Transfer the remaining bulgur to a large bowl.
prep_instructions.4: Coat the baking sheet with cooking spray and place the kofta patties on it. Broil, turning once, until an instant-read thermometer registers 160°F, 10 to 12 minutes total.
prep_instructions.5: Meanwhile, add kale, tomatoes, feta, oil, vinegar, oregano, the slivered onion and the remaining ¼ teaspoon each salt and pepper to the bulgur; gently toss to combine. Serve with the kofta.

prep_instructions.1: Preheat your oven to 400 degrees F. Lightly coat a baking sheet with cooking spray. Cut each chicken breast in half lengthwise so that you have 4 pieces total. Pound each piece to an even 1/2-inch thickness. Set aside.
prep_instructions.2: In a wide, shallow bowl (a pie dish works well), combine the Italian breadcrumbs, whole wheat Panko breadcrumbs, Parmesan, garlic powder, and pepper. In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg whites until lightly foamy. Cut the mozzarella into 4 slices, or grate and divide into four equal portions.
prep_instructions.3: Arrange your work station in the following order: pounded chicken, egg whites, breadcrumb mixture, baking sheet. Working one at a time, dip each piece of chicken into the egg whites, shaking off any excess, then the breadcrumbs, gently patting the chicken as needed so that the crumbs stick to all sides. Place on the prepared baking sheet. Lightly coat the tops of the chicken with baking spray.
prep_instructions.4: Bake until the chicken is cooked through (it should reach an internal temperature of 165 degrees F) and the crumbs are brown, about 15 minutes. Remove from the oven, spoon 2 tablespoons of sauce over each piece of chicken, and top with a slice of mozzarella. Return to the oven and bake until the cheese is melted, about 3-5 additional minutes. Sprinkle with basil and enjoy immediately, topped with extra sauce as desired.

prep_instructions.1: Chop the romaine into bite-sized pieces and layer into the bottom of a wide bowl, or if you are meal prepping use 4 air tight containers. Prep veggies, and chop chicken breast into 1/2″-1″ pieces.
prep_instructions.2: Layer cheese, black beans, tomatoes, chicken, corn, and red onion on top of the lettuce, then sprinkle with cilantro.
prep_instructions.3: Place the baked corn chips around the side of the bowl, or if you are meal prepping in small containers, put these in a baggie on the side so they don’t get soggy from the moisture of the salad.
prep_instructions.4: Right before serving, toss the salad with the skinny salsa ranch.
prep_instructions.5: Meanwhile, add kale, tomatoes, feta, oil, vinegar, oregano, the slivered onion and the remaining ¼ teaspoon each salt and pepper to the bulgur; gently toss to combine. Serve with the kofta.

prep_instructions.1: In a large bowl, whisk together the mashed banana and peanut butter until smooth. Stir in the eggs until evenly combined. Next, stir in the maple syrup, chia seeds, vanilla, and cinnamon. Sprinkle the baking soda, then the oat flour, over the top. Fold to combine. Last, fold in the pepitas, cranberries, and raisins. The batter will look very liquidy. Place the bowl in the refrigerator to chill and set for at least 4 hours, or cover with plastic and refrigerate overnight.
prep_instructions.2: When ready to bake, place a rack in the center of your oven and preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat. With a large cookie scoop or spoon, portion the batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto the prepared cookie sheet. If needed, shape them lightly with your fingers so that they are round and slightly flat on top.  Bake for 12 to 14 minutes, until the cookies feel dry and set on the top and edges and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Let cool on the pan for 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to finish cooling completely.

prep_instructions.1: In a pot combine 1 cup rice and 2 cups of water. Close the lid and cook for 25–30 minutes or until the rice absorbs the water (over low heat). Set aside.
prep_instructions.2: In a big bowl add ground turkey, green peas, corn and seasonings. Mix well with a spatula or use your hands :) Scoop ground turkey mixture into a measuring spoon/cup/tool for each patties. Roll and press with your hands for little patties.
prep_instructions.3: Preheat a non-stick pan over medium heat. Spray olive oil and cook patties 5 minutes per side (Do not burn them).
prep_instructions.4: After patties are ready, use the same pan for baby spinach. Spray coconut/olive oil and sautée baby spinach for 2 -3 minutes.
prep_instructions.5: After baby spinach, use the same pan again for the fried coconut-papaya rice! :) Spray pan with coconut oil spray (we want to add a tropical flavor). Add 2 cups of cooked rice and coconut milk. Stir & cook 3 minutes. Add in the papaya chunks. Stir & cook another 3 minutes.
prep_instructions.6: Serve everything evenly into containers with cherry tomatoes.

prep_instructions.1: Assemble the burritos, optionally toast, and enjoy!
In a medium bowl add, diced pineapple, red pepper, red onion, cilantro, chipotle pepper, lime juice, and salt to taste. Lightly toss to mix.
prep_instructions.2: In a small bowl add, avocado, juice of 1 lime, and salt to taste. Gently smash the avocado and stir, it will look like a chunky guacamole. Set both the pineapple salsa and smashed avocado aside.
prep_instructions.3: Remove salmon and bring to room temperature, pat dry.
prep_instructions.4: In a small bowl add smoked paprika, garlic powder, chipotle chili powder, and sea salt. Stir. Season the flesh side of salmon with seasoning. Rub mixture into salmon to completely cover it.
prep_instructions.5: Heat large skillet to medium high heat.
prep_instructions.6: Add canola oil to the pan. Place salmon on pan flesh side down. Saute for 4-6 minutes. Using a flat spatula gently flip the salmon and saute the on the skin side for another 4-6 minutes until crispy. You’ll know the salmon is done when it starts to turn opaque or if the fish feels firm instead of spongy when you touch it. Remove from the pan and let sit.
prep_instructions.7: Add tortillas directly on the burners and brown until crispy. You want the tortilla to be like a hard shell taco but not burnt.
prep_instructions.8: With a fork, gently flake the salmon apart.
prep_instructions.9: Assemble the tostadas. Start with tortilla on the bottom, smear 1-2 tablespoons of avocado on tostada, pile shredded salmon on top, and finish with pineapple salsa.
prep_instructions.10: Finish with a squeeze of fresh lime juice and serve!

prep_instructions.1: Steam cauliflower in a large pot of water over high heat. Cook until cauliflower is completely soft.
prep_instructions.2: While you wait for the cauliflower to soften, switch crockpot to high. Once the base is hot, add your onions and beef to the pot to start browning the meat and sautéing the onions. Salt to taste.
prep_instructions.3: Turn crockpot down to low. Add mushrooms and water.
prep_instructions.4: Drain your cauliflower and put it in a food processor with the garlic. The cauliflower should be soft enough to puree without adding any liquids.
prep_instructions.5: Empty the cauliflower into the crockpot with the rest of your stew. The cauliflower creates the creamy texture and takes on the flavor of the beef, mushrooms and onion. Delicious!
prep_instructions.6: Add a tsp. of Worcestershire sauce and stir the pot until all ingredients are well combined.

prep_instructions.1: Bring a small pot of water to a boil. Using a long-handled spoon, gently lower the eggs into the water. Roughly dropping them in can cause the shells to crack on the bottom of the pot.
prep_instructions.2: Turn the heat down to a gentle simmer and set a timer for 6 minutes. Carefully remove the cooked eggs and submerge in an ice bath or run under cold water until cool enough to handle. Tap each egg gently on the counter and roll to crack the shell all over. Peel the shell off.
prep_instructions.3: Arrange the mozzarella and tomato slices on a plate and nestle the eggs into the center so they’re secure. Drizzle with the olive oil, sprinkle with basil, season with salt and pepper and slice open the eggs so that the yolk runs all over.

prep_instructions.1: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line a 9-by-5-inch loaf pan with parchment paper, letting the paper extend a few
prep_instructions.2: In a medium bowl, whisk together the applesauce, maple syrup, coconut sugar, almond butter, almond milk and vanilla extract until smooth.
prep_instructions.3: In a large bowl, combine 1¾ cups of the spelt flour, the rolled oats, cinnamon, baking powder, ginger, nutmeg, allspice, baking soda and salt.
prep_instructions.4: Pour the wet ingredients into the dry, stirring to combine with a wooden spoon until well incorporated.
prep_instructions.5: In a small bowl, combine the blueberries with the remaining 2 tablespoons spelt flour, tossing to coat (this prevents the blueberries from sinking to the bottom of the cake). Using a rubber spatula, fold the blueberries and chopped pistachios into the cake batter. Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan.
prep_instructions.6: Bake the loaf until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes. Allow to cool in the pan on top of a wire rack, then lift the bread out of the pan using the parchment as handles. Serve warm or at room temperature.

prep_instructions.1: Preheat the oven to 400°F.
prep_instructions.2: In a medium pot, cover the potato with at least 1 inch of water and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Boil until the potato is fork-tender, 22 to 25 minutes.
prep_instructions.3: Drain the potato, slice it into thin rounds and set aside.
prep_instructions.4: Heat the olive oil in a small, oven-safe skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and zucchini; season with salt and pepper. Sauté until tender, about 4 minutes.
prep_instructions.5: Add the potato slices and sauté until all the veggies are lightly browned, 5 to 7 minutes. Spread the vegetables into an even layer in the base of the pan. Remove the skillet from the heat.
prep_instructions.6: Whisk the eggs together in a medium bowl and pour them over the vegetables. Top the eggs with the cheese.
prep_instructions.7: Transfer the skillet to the oven and bake until the eggs are set and the potato and zucchini slices on the top are golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
prep_instructions.8: Serve the tortilla warm or at room temperature with the side salad.

prep_instructions.1: Preheat the oven to 350°F.
prep_instructions.2: In a large, oven-safe skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the onion and sauté until tender, 4 to 5 minutes. Add the garlic and jalapeño, then sauté until fragrant, 1 minute more.
prep_instructions.3: Stir in the spinach and cook until fully wilted if using fresh, 4 to 5 minutes, or until heated through if thawed from frozen, 1 to 2 minutes.
prep_instructions.4: Season with cumin, coriander, salt, pepper and harissa. Cook about 1 minute, until fragrant.
prep_instructions.5: Transfer the mixture to the bowl of a food processor or a blender and puree until coarse. Add the broth and puree until thick and smooth.
prep_instructions.6: Wipe out the skillet and grease it with nonstick cooking spray. Pour the spinach mixture back into the pan and use a wooden spoon to make eight circular wells.
prep_instructions.7: Gently crack the eggs into the wells. Transfer the skillet to the oven and cook until the egg whites are fully set, but the yolks are still a little bit jiggly, 20 to 25 minutes.
prep_instructions.8: Sprinkle the shakshuka with parsley, cilantro and red-pepper flakes, to taste. Serve immediately.

19.name of recipe: Hearty Roasted Veggie Salad with Chicken

prep_instructions.1: Wash and cube the sweet potato with the skin on. Then wash, peel, and cube the beet root. In a bowl toss both with some of the olive oil, balsamic, thyme, and garlic salt.
prep_instructions.2: On a large parchment paper lined baking tray spread these evenly over the entire pan. Place in a 380° F (190° C) oven for about 75 minutes.
prep_instructions.3: Cut up the onion and red bell pepper into medium sized pieces. In the bowl, now toss these with some olive oil, balsamic, thyme, and garlic salt.
prep_instructions.4: On a large parchment paper lined baking tray, spread the onion and pepper pieces evenly over the entire pan. Place in the oven for the last 30 minutes of the sweet potato and beet root’s cooking time.
prep_instructions.5: While the veggies are roasting prepare the salad, cut the cucumber, and divide evenly over 2 or 3 large salad bowls.
prep_instructions.6: Butterfly the chicken breasts and coat with a little olive oil and salt & pepper. Cook on a hot grill about 5 minutes on each side. When cooked cut the chicken into strips.
prep_instructions.7: When the veggies are roasted, divide them evenly over the beds of salad and then top each with the chicken strips.
prep_instructions.8: Serve with your favorite dressing. Works well with a balsamic vinaigrette, ranch, or even honey mustard.

20.name of recipe: Boneless Turkey Burgers with Savory Warm Relish

prep_instructions.1: Wash and dry the lettuce leaves.
prep_instructions.2: In a large skillet sauté the onion, pepper, and red cabbage with the olive oil until soft.
prep_instructions.3: Add the garlic salt and balsamic vinegar and allow to simmer until the vinegar and veggies are shiny and caramelized. Stir often. (Most of the liquid will have cooked off).
prep_instructions.4: Keep this relish warm.
prep_instructions.5: Grill or pan fry 4 quarter pound turkey burgers until just done. (Cooking them too long will make them dry) Usually 4 minutes on each side on a hot grill is sufficient, but a little longer if you are using the frozen type.
prep_instructions.6: Now place a turkey burger on the stem end of the lettuce leaf, top with a generous portion of the warm relish.

prep_instructions.1: Combine all dry into a bowl.
prep_instructions.2: Mix in yogurt to form a protein pudding.
prep_instructions.3: Get a sheet of wax paper and lie it on a kitchen table.
prep_instructions.4: Dip Strawberries in protein pudding, and drop on wax paper.
prep_instructions.5: Rinse/Repeat until all pudding/strawberries have been used.

prep_instructions.1: Start by mixing your Dry in a bowl (Whey, Pancake Mix, Baking Powder, Splenda, SF/FF Pudding Mix)
prep_instructions.2: Add in Wet (Water/Egg White/ and Greek Yogurt) and stir with a spoon until batter like consistency is formed.
prep_instructions.3: Pre-heat griddle on a medium power which is on the stove, and spray with cooking spray.
prep_instructions.4: Drop in circles and let cook for 2 minutes on one side, flip, and then finish the other side and set the pancakes aside.
prep_instructions.5: Apply cooking spray to same skillet. Mix egg whites and set aside after cooked.
prep_instructions.6: Take eggs and put between pancakes and top with cheese.

prep_instructions.1: Combine dry ingredients into a mixing bowl.
prep_instructions.2: Add wet ingredients and stir to form batter.
prep_instructions.3: Coat a circular tupperware container with cooking spray and transfer batter.
prep_instructions.4: Microwave on medium power for 3-3.5 minutes
prep_instructions.5: Transfer cake to a separate plate (use a fork to separate edges along tupperware)
prep_instructions.6: Take Vanilla Protein and add a touch of water to form a glaze in a small container.
prep_instructions.7: Cut small hole in top of cake, remove center, and use the glaze as a filling. It will gooze off the side of the cake hence "lava cake".
prep_instructions.8: Top with crushed up graham crackers.

prep_instructions.1: Pre-Heat oven to 350 degrees.
prep_instructions.2: Combine all dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
prep_instructions.3: Combine wet ingredients with dry and form batter.
prep_instructions.4: Coat a Pyrex dish with cooking spray and fill batter into dish and place in the oven for 20-25 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean in the center.
prep_instructions.5: Pull out of oven and place on cooling rack. Allow to cool for 5-10 minutes.

prep_instructions.1: Pre-Heat oven to 350 degrees.
prep_instructions.2: Combine dry ingredients into a mixing bowl (place some sprinkles in batter)
prep_instructions.3: Add wet ingredients and stir to form batter
prep_instructions.4: Coat a circular donut pan with cooking spray and transfer batter
prep_instructions.5: Bake for 12-15 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean
prep_instructions.6: Transfer donuts to a seperate plate
prep_instructions.7: Mix Whey and yogurt to form a thick pudding (this is your glaze)
prep_instructions.8: Take a donut, dip it into the glaze, let the remaining glaze drip over the bowl, and set it on a plate
prep_instructions.9: Garnish top of the donuts with sprinkles and crushed up cereal

prep_instructions.1: Pre-Heat oven to 350 degrees.
prep_instructions.2: Use a blender to grind oatmeal to a fine powder. Combine grinded oatmeal with dry ingredients in a mixing bowl and set aside
prep_instructions.3: Add wet ingredients and mix to form batter
prep_instructions.4: Use aluminum foil to line a baking sheet. Coat with cooking spray. Drop cookies 1 apart from each other with a spoon on coated baking sheet. Place the Reese pieces on top before baking
prep_instructions.5: Bake 7-9 Minutes (top with start to turn golden brown)
prep_instructions.6: Allow to cool for 5 minutes & Enjoy

prep_instructions.1: Pre-Heat Waffle Iron.
prep_instructions.2: Remove skin from Sweet potato. Microwave for 1 minute and set aside.
prep_instructions.3: In a mixing bowl add the rest of the dry and then grate the sweet potato.
prep_instructions.4: Add wet ingredients to form batter
prep_instructions.5: Coat Waffle Iron (Once pre-heated) with cooking spray and drop batter. Cook Until All waffle batter is used.

prep_instructions.1: Make Protein Pudding with Yogurt + Whey
prep_instructions.2: Grab a Muffin Sheet and place cupcake lines in holes
prep_instructions.3: Place a small layer of protein pudding on bottom and freeze for 30 minutes
prep_instructions.4: Pull out and add peanut butter in center freeze another 30 minutes
prep_instructions.5: Add final layer of Protein Pudding and freeze for another 30 minutes till they harden
prep_instructions.6: Pull apart the cupcake liner and enjoy

prep_instructions.1: In a large bowl, mix lime juice, oil, vinegar, soy sauce, and fish sauce.
prep_instructions.2: Remove meat from the rotisserie chicken and toss in the sauce mixture.
prep_instructions.3: Divide cabbage and carrots between bowls and top with chicken.
prep_instructions.4: Top each with peanuts and cilantro.

prep_instructions.1: Rinse the chicken under running water and pat dry with paper towel.
prep_instructions.2: Add chicken, potatoes, garlic to a large bowl and sprinkle with salt, pepper, crumbled bouillon cube and Cajun spice.
prep_instructions.3: Drizzle with olive oil and toss everything to coat well.
prep_instructions.4: Marinate in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.
prep_instructions.5: Meanwhile preheat your oven to 430°F.
prep_instructions.6: Place in the oven and bake for 25 minutes.
prep_instructions.7: Add red onions then lower the oven to 360°F and bake for 15 minutes.
prep_instructions.8: Check for doneness, if the potatoes and chicken are soft and easily pierced with a fork, they are ready. If the chicken and vegetables have not browned up as much as you would like, just broil for 5 minutes, watching carefully not to burn the chicken.
